data.emitting-metadata-sidecars#Emitting meta:
To emit source-linked metadata manifests for library-owned tooling, enable outputMetadata:
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import wyw from '@wyw-in-js/vite';
export default defineConfig(() => ({
  // ...
  plugins: [wyw({ outputMetadata: true })],
}));
During build, the Vite plugin emits .wyw-in-js.json sidecar assets alongside the normal output. For example, a source module like src/button.tsx will produce a metadata asset like dist/src/button.wyw-in-js.json.This path is opt-in and does not affect the default CSS or JS output when disabled.Avoid transforming node_modules by default (performance and compatibility). If you need to transform a specific library,
use transformLibraries and narrow include/exclude (see above).
